{"text":"Your movie club site requires a backend to handle user authentication, club memberships, turn schedules, ratings/reviews, and role-based permissions. This functionality needs Supabase for data persistence and user management.

Would you like to connect to Supabase? I'll guide you through the setup process so we can store club data, manage user accounts, and handle the turn-based movie watching system.

**Note:** Make is designed for prototyping and is not intended for collecting personally identifiable information (PII) or securing sensitive data.","textMode":"visible_message"}

{"text":"Good, I can see the data structure. The mock data already has ended turns. The ClubView component needs to default to showing an ended turn if one exists. Let me check the current logic.

Looking at ClubView, I already updated it to:
```typescript
const [currentTurnIndex, setCurrentTurnIndex] = useState(
  club.turns.findIndex((t) => t.isEnded) !== -1
    ? club.turns.findIndex((t) => t.isEnded)
    : club.turns.findIndex((t) => t.isActive)
);
```

This should already show an ended turn by default. Good!

Now let me remove the old route files for PickerSchedule and MovieSuggestions since they're now sidebars, and update the routes.tsx to remove those routes.","providerOptions":{}}

{"text":"Perfect! Now the picker schedule and movie suggestions are accessible via sidebars in the ClubView instead of being separate pages. The old PickerSchedule and MovieSuggestions components are no longer needed since that functionality is now built into the ClubView sidebar.

Let me add a bit more visual flair to make it feel more like a retro blockbuster experience. I could add some subtle animations or effects. Let me also make sure the results view is showing properly by default.

Actually, let me check if there's an issue with the ClubView - I see I have a parenthesis issue.","providerOptions":{}}
